				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$ \Delta G_{X}^{i} \left[ 0 \right] = \Delta G_{AX}^{\circ } \left[ { - 1} \right] - \Delta G_{A}^{\circ } \left[ { - 1} \right] $$\end{document}The intrinsic binding energy is associated with a zero value of ΔN and is therefore independent of C°. Jencks [51] writes the ΔG° value for a compound with linked groups A and B in its molecular structure as the sum of the intrinsic binding energies of A and B, and the “connection Gibbs energy” (ΔGs):7ΔGAB∘-1=ΔGAi0+ΔGBi0+ΔGs-1\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
